<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,361,1252]" box="[151,1025,361,388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,361,387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Description.</emphasis>
Ground coloration brown, forewing with large yellow markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,361,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
Small sized. Head distinctly wider than pronotum, anterior margin of crown in dorsal view round, crown slightly shorter medially than next to eyes (
<figureCitation box="[582,672,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[209,1362,189,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[185,1401,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, hind tibia, posterior view; D, hind tibia, anterior view; E, adult, lateral view; F, forewing; G, pygofer; side and male subgential plate, lateral view H, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view I, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars: A–E = 1mm; G– I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Ocelli hyaline, around with black markings, situated near ends of lateral frontal sutures (
<figureCitation box="[401,486,470,496]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[209,1362,189,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[185,1401,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, hind tibia, posterior view; D, hind tibia, anterior view; E, adult, lateral view; F, forewing; G, pygofer; side and male subgential plate, lateral view H, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view I, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars: A–E = 1mm; G– I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Face, without median longitudinal ridges, lateral margins broadly convex; anteclypeus flat, short and wide, constricted medially; upper part of face with fine arcuate striations (
<figureCitation box="[1172,1259,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[209,1362,189,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[185,1401,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, hind tibia, posterior view; D, hind tibia, anterior view; E, adult, lateral view; F, forewing; G, pygofer; side and male subgential plate, lateral view H, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view I, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars: A–E = 1mm; G– I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Pronotum and scutellum each broader than long. subapical cells; appendix wider than inner apical cell and bordering inner three anteapical cells (
<figureCitation box="[341,427,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[209,1362,189,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[185,1401,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, hind tibia, posterior view; D, hind tibia, anterior view; E, adult, lateral view; F, forewing; G, pygofer; side and male subgential plate, lateral view H, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view I, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars: A–E = 1mm; G– I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with several stout and long macrosetae, AV with 4 macrosetae in distal half, PV with ~15 macrosetae becoming longer distally, AD with 6–7 macrosetae and PD with 13–14 macrosetae. Hind femur apical macrosetae formula 2 + 0 (
<figureCitation box="[601,724,650,676]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[209,1362,189,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[185,1401,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, hind tibia, posterior view; D, hind tibia, anterior view; E, adult, lateral view; F, forewing; G, pygofer; side and male subgential plate, lateral view H, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view I, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars: A–E = 1mm; G– I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 1C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,361,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis box="[199,373,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer nearly triangular in lateral view, with vertical cleft dorsally near base and membranous area medially; processes absent. Subgenital plates ligulate, approximately as long as pygofer, dorsal margin with dense slender setae. Style moderately long, middle area of apophysis wide, constricted preapically with dense preapical patch of long, fine setae; apex truncate with two acute points. Connective relatively short and narrow with pair of short anterior arms and broad, emarginate stem. Aedeagal shaft slender, slightly asymmetrical, strongly curved dorsad in lateral view, with single (unpaired) long retrorse dorsal process arising preapically and extended based; gonopore large, near midlength of shaft on posterior surface (
<figureCitation box="[917,1006,902,928]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[209,1362,189,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[185,1401,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, hind tibia, posterior view; D, hind tibia, anterior view; E, adult, lateral view; F, forewing; G, pygofer; side and male subgential plate, lateral view H, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view I, aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars: A–E = 1mm; G– I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651331/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,361,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis box="[199,397,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Female ovipositor strongly projecting beyond pygofer. Sternite VII truncate posteriorly (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,248,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,424,1257]" captionTargetId="figure-111@3.[151,1435,417,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, female genitalia, ventral view; B, Sternite VII; C, first valvula of ovipositor, lateral view; D, apex of second valvula of ovipositor, lateral view; E, second valvula of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651333/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). First valvulae with striate sculpturing (
<figureCitation box="[655,745,974,1000]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,248,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,424,1257]" captionTargetId="figure-111@3.[151,1435,417,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, female genitalia, ventral view; B, Sternite VII; C, first valvula of ovipositor, lateral view; D, apex of second valvula of ovipositor, lateral view; E, second valvula of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651333/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Second valvula abruptly beyond midlength in lateral view, dorsal margin of distal part arcuate with numerous irregular teeth (
<figureCitation box="[896,963,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,248,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,424,1257]" captionTargetId="figure-111@3.[151,1435,417,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Longiaedeagus flavofasciatus sp. nov. A, female genitalia, ventral view; B, Sternite VII; C, first valvula of ovipositor, lateral view; D, apex of second valvula of ovipositor, lateral view; E, second valvula of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4651333/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C–E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
