<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="147" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,361,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1082,1108]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new generic name is derived from the words “ 
<emphasis box="[918,976,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">longi</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis box="[1057,1163,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">aedeagus</emphasis>
”, indicating that the aedeagus is slender. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="147" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,361,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1154,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Remark.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Dai, 2021" authorityName="Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Dai" authorityYear="2021" box="[312,483,1154,1180]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Longiaedeagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,483,1154,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Longiaedeagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[491,597,1154,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[491,597,1154,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Xue &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Xue &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[746,1065,1154,1180]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Lambirocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[746,902,1154,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Lambirocerus</emphasis>
Xue &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
in the long and slender aedeagal shaft and forewing venation, but this new genus can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Xue &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[1015,1171,1190,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Lambirocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1171,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Lambirocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the broad style, aedeagus apex not bifurcation, and subapical with long and wide processes in ventral marginal.
</paragraph>
